Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C and put a large #saucepan{} of water with a pinch of
@salt{pinch} on to boil for the potato. Remove the root and dark green top from
the @leek{1}(sliced into 2cm thick rounds) and slice into 2cm thick rounds. Remove
the top and bottom from the @carrot{1}(peeled and quartered lengthways),
then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into small pieces. Trim the
@radishes{125}(trimmed and cut in half), then cut in half. Chop the
@potatoes{450%g}(chopped into 2cm chunks) into 2cm chunks (no need to peel!).
Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Put the @British chicken thighs{4} in a #mixing bowl{} with the
@spiced honey mustard{2}, a drizzle of oil and a pinch of @salt{} and
@ground black pepper{}. Mix together so the chicken gets a nice coating.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat!

Add the potato to the pan of boiling water and cook for ~{15-20%minutes}.

> TIP: The potato is cooked when you can easily slip a knife through.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan with the lid on.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot,
add the chicken and cook until browned, ~{2-3%minutes} on each side. Transfer to
a lined #baking tray{} and roast on the top shelf of your oven for
~{15%minutes} (don't wash the pan - you'll need it later).

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, remove from your oven and allow it to rest for a few minutes.

In the meantime, heat a drizzle of oil in the now empty pan on medium heat. Add
the leek, carrot and radish. Cook until golden, ~{5%minutes}. Stir in the
@chicken stock powder{1} and @water{100%ml} (see ingredients for amount). Cover
loosely with #foil{}. Reduce the heat to low and simmer until the veggies are
soft and the liquid has reduced by three-quarters, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Roughly chop the parsley (stalks and all). Add half the parsley to the drained
potato along with a pinch of salt and pepper. Add the @Flora Original{20%g} and
mash until smooth with a #potato masher{}, then pop the lid on to keep your mash
warm and leave to the side.

When the veggies are ready, stir in a knob of @?butter{}. Serve the honey mustard
chicken with the braised veggies and mash on the side. Sprinkle over the
remaining parsley. Enjoy!